"{\"uid\": \"rte.ie-sport-paris-2024-2024-0731-1462858-paris-2024-wiffen-hardly-slept-after-olympic-gold-win\", \"text\": \"  Olympic gold medallist Daniel Wiffen said he hardly slept after his 800m freestyle triumph.  The 23-year-old Armagh manstormed the final stretchin the La Defense Arena to clinch gold in an Olympic record time last night.  After receiving his medal on the podium, Wiffen said he went straight into anti-doping and then the swim-down before treating himself to some pizza.  \\\"We left the pool at 12.30am, got back into the dining hall, had a couple slices of pizza, then tried to go to bed - did not happen,\\\" he said.  \\\"Got to bed at about 3.30am and woke up at 7.30 this morning. I did not get too much sleep but that's not surprising.  \\\"I watched it (the race) before I went to sleep because I knew I would not sleep so I watched it and I am very happy, it was paced to perfection, that's all we can ask for.  \\\"Words can not describe how you feel when you wake up and next to your pillow is an Olympic gold medal.\\\"  Gold medal winner Daniel Wiffen speaks to RT\\u00c9 Sport the day after winning gold in the 800m freestyle#RTESport#Paris2024\\ud83d\\udcfa Watchhttps://t.co/b2OI4OoWVJ\\ud83d\\udcf1Updateshttps://t.co/01ShZjM17Cpic.twitter.com/oPd5qDaC0d  Wiffen's family - including his twin brother Nathan - were poolside to witness his stunning victory.  He said: \\\"It was amazing to see my twin brother in the crowd, you can not ask for more than that, then my whole family being there.  \\\"Words just can not describe, seeing my mum crying and that setting me off. And the national anthem, tears going down my face. I have kind of forgotten it because it's gone so quick, but it's so cool.  \\\"My parents have been driving me to 4.30am practice, it's been a relentless journey. I have been doing this since I was at least 12-years-old and they kept doing it for me and they are the reason I am here today.  \\\"They are a massive part, and that's why I say it's never an individual sport, swimming, I have got this whole support network behind me.\\\"  Read more:Meet Daniel Wiffen - Ireland's gold medal winning swimmer  Wiffen will now be eyeing more success in the 1500m freestyle, with the heats due to start on Saturday morning.  He said he will return to training tonight and temporarily put his 800m win \\\"under the bed\\\".  \\\"I am taking it in my stride, the 1500 is in a couple of days. Today is about getting all the emotions out and then tonight I will get back to training. I wanted to swim this morning, I miss the pool already.  \\\"I am going to refocus, forget about this race, put it under the bed after this morning and I will revisit it when I am finished.\\\"  Watch the 2024 Olympic Games with 14 hours of televised action on RT\\u00c92 and RT\\u00c9 Player each day.  Listen to extensive radio coverage on RT\\u00c9 Radio 1 and 2fm's Game On and follow each moment from Paris on RT\\u00c9.ie, the RT\\u00c9 News app and all RT\\u00c9 digital platforms. Listen to the daily RT\\u00c9 Sport Olympics Podcast.  \\u00a9 RT\\u00c9 2026. RT\\u00c9.ie is the website of Raidi\\u00f3 Teilif\\u00eds \\u00c9ireann, Ireland's National Public Service Media. RT\\u00c9 is not responsible for the content of external internet sites.  Images Courtesy of Getty Images.\"}"